''''|\u751f\u5f92\u4f1a\u5f79\u54e1\u5171||\"Student Council Staff Members\"|lead=y}} is a Japanese [[Yonkoma|four-panel]] [[manga]] series written and illustrated by Tozen Ujiie. The series began serialization in the June 2007 issue of [[Kodansha]]'s ''[[Magazine Special]]'' and ran in that magazine until the July 2008 issue, where it was thereafter transferred to Kodansha's ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Magazine]]'' in September 2008, and has been running there since. Chapters are collected and published in collected volumes by [[Kodansha]], with eighteen volumes released as of August 2019 in Japan. A 13-episode [[anime]] television series adaptation animated by [[GoHands]] aired in Japan between July and September 2010 and has been licensed by [[Sentai Filmworks]]. A second anime season aired between January and March 2014. An anime film premiered in July 2017, and a second anime film will premiere in July 2020.\n\n==Plot==\nTakatoshi Tsuda attends \u014csai Academy, a high school that, due to declining birth rates, is converted from an [[Single-sex education|all-girl school]] to a [[Mixed-sex education|co-ed school]] (with a male-to-female ratio of 28:524). On his first day, he is forcibly recruited into the [[student council]] as the vice-president and sole male representative. The story follows Tsuda and the student council as they interact with each other and their schoolmates.\n\n==Characters==\n<!-- Please provide citations to manga chapters, anime episodes, official profiles, or author notes / critics reviews that explain the character and its development -->\n\n===Main characters===\n;Takatoshi Tsuda\n;{{voiced by|[[Shintar\u014d Asanuma]].<ref name=\"dvd9cdjapan\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=NEOBK-1479257|title=Seitokai Yakuindomo 9 (Limited Edition) w/ Anime DVD|publisher=CD Japan|accessdate=October 10, 2013}}</ref>}}\n:{{Nihongo|Takatoshi Tsuda|\u6d25\u7530 \u30bf\u30ab\u30c8\u30b7|Tsuda Takatoshi}} is the main character of the story. He chooses to attend a former all-girl school simply because it is close to his home.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} On his first day at the school, he is forcibly recruited into the student council as the vice-president and male representative.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} He normally acts as the [[tsukkomi|straight-man]] to Shino and Aria, who, along with other girls in the school, regularly make perverted comments and sexual innuendos. Eventually, he becomes so used to this behaviour that he actually feels odd when they do not make such jokes.<ref name=\"ep3\">''Seitokai Yakuindomo'' TV series, episode 3.</ref><ref name=\"ep5\">''Seitokai Yakuindomo'' TV series, episode 5.</ref>\n\n;Shino Amakusa\n;{{voiced by|[[Y\u014dko Hikasa]]<ref name=\"dvd9cdjapan\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|Shino Amakusa|\u5929\u8349 \u30b7\u30ce|Amakusa Shino}} is a second-year student and the student council president.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} She is serious and diligent, excels in academics, and is very popular among the student body.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p2, p3}} However, she is almost always thinking perverted things. She suggests that one of her original reasons she showed an interest in Takatoshi is so that she could observe him in health and physical education classes.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} Although she has excellent grades and is skilled in a wide range of subjects, she [[Acrophobia|fears heights]]{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p2, p10}} and [[Entomophobia|insects]],{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 2}} and her rather flat chest makes her feel self-conscious,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p10}} especially when comparing herself to Aria.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p13}} She occasionally performs couple-like activities with Takatoshi such as walking with him, sharing an umbrella or clearing his earwax, but gets embarrassed whenever Takatoshi says anything that could be interpreted as being romantic (as the series progresses, it is hinted she has feelings for Takatoshi, though she has denied it when directly asked).<ref name=ep11>''Seitokai Yakuindomo'' TV series, episode 11</ref> According to her childhood friend Misaki Amano, Shino was student council president at her previous school.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 60|:extra}}\n\n;Aria Shichijo\n;{{voiced by|[[Satomi Sat\u014d]]<ref name=\"dvd9cdjapan\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|Aria Shichij\u014d|\u4e03\u6761 \u30a2\u30ea\u30a2|Shichij\u014d Aria}} is the student council secretary and in the same year as Shino;{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} they are good friends.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p11}} She comes from an affluent family and is the most physically mature character. However, she has a strongly perverted mind; like Shino, she has a habit of twisting every word and thought into something sexual.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1, p4, p5}} Because she is absurdly rich and overly pampered,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p5}} she can be a social airhead: for instance, she will wait in front of a door and expect it to slide open{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p10}} or stand at the bottom of a staircase expecting it to be an escalator.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p7}}  In contrast, she is academically smart and places second in midterms for her class year, right behind Shino.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p4}} Her chest is larger than Shino's,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p4}} which causes the latter to feel self-conscious.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p10, p13}}\n\n;Suzu Hagimura\n;{{voiced by|[[Sayuri Yahagi]]<ref name=\"dvd9cdjapan\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|Suzu Hagimura|\u8429\u6751 \u30b9\u30ba|Hagimura Suzu}} is the student council treasurer and in the same year as Takatoshi.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} She describes herself as a returning student with an IQ of 180, can do 10-digit arithmetic calculations in her head,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} and is fluent in multiple languages including English.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1, p6}} Even though she is 16 years old at the start of the series, she is no taller than an elementary school student and is [[Napoleon complex|very sensitive about her short stature]].{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p1}} Many of the jokes involve her childish appearance or height and she flies into a rage whenever such subjects are mentioned. Although initially reluctant to accept Takatoshi as a member of the student council, she soon becomes dependent on him, to the point of feeling uneasy when he's not around, and it is hinted on multiple occasions later in the series that she may be developing feelings for him. In situations where multiple characters are conversing, often only the top of her head is shown,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p14}} or a caption and arrow points to where she is.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p5, 1}}\n\n===Supporting characters===\n<!--- This is mainly a list of the characters that have profiles in the front of the volumes. Others can be added if notable. --->\n;Ranko Hata\n;{{voiced by|[[Satomi Arai]]<ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\">{{cite web|url=http://www.starchild.co.jp/special/seitokai2/s-council/staff_cast.html |title=\u751f\u5f92\u4f1a\u5f79\u54e1\u5171\uff0a\uff5c\u751f\u5f92\u4f1a\u5f79\u54e1\u5171\uff5c\u30b9\u30bf\u30c3\u30d5\u30fb\u30ad\u30e3\u30b9\u30c8 |work=StarChild |date= |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Ranko Hata}}|\u7551 \u30e9\u30f3\u30b3|Hata Ranko}} is the head of the school's newspaper club.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p3}} She likes to take photos of the student council members to sell around the school, usually without the permission of those being photographed,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 1, 7}} and she often gets caught. When she conducts an interview, she likes to twist the responses to something dirty or perverted, with Tsuda as a frequent target{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p3, 1}}; running gags in the series have her constantly trying to get Shino and Takatoshi to admit that they are dating, or her admitting to spreading rumors about it, much to their chagrin. She is expressionless{{gnr|vol|3}} and has a [[deadpan]] monotone voice in the anime, which strongly contrasts with the other girls' excitable temperaments.\n\n;Mutsumi Mitsuba\n;{{voiced by|[[Chiaki Omigawa]]<ref name=\"dvd9cdjapan\"/><ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Mutsumi Mitsuba}}|\u4e09\u8449 \u30e0\u30c4\u30df|Mitsuba Mutsumi}} is Takatoshi's classmate who forms a judo club at the start of the series.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p4}} She is dedicated to leading her club but is also simple-minded.<ref name=\"ep5\"/> She develops a crush on Takatoshi later in the series and, despite her remarkable potential and drive regarding martial arts, states that her dream is to simply become a bride.<ref name=\"ep11\" /> In one instance, she combines his family name {{Nihongo|Tsuda|\u6d25\u7530}} with her given name {{Nihongo|Mutsumi|\u30e0\u30c4\u30df}}.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 151}} Because of her innocent nature, she often misses Aria and Shino's innuendos.<ref name=\"ep8\">''Seitokai Yakuindomo'' TV series, episode 8</ref>\n\n;Naruko Yokoshima\n;{{voiced by|[[Y\u016b Kobayashi]]<ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Naruko Yokoshima}}|\u6a2a\u5cf6 \u30ca\u30eb\u30b3|Yokoshima Naruko}} is a teacher at \u014csai Academy and the student council adviser.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p5}} She is even more perverted than Aria and Shino and [[cougar (slang)|aggressively seeks out younger guys]], not excepting her male students.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p5}}<ref name=\"ep5\"/> In the anime, she teaches English and, true to form, her syllabus almost always contains perverted content.<ref name=\"ep5\"/> She is perceived to be unreliable by the council members and useless as an educator.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 4}}\n\n;Kotomi Tsuda\n;{{voiced by|[[Asami Shimoda]]<ref name=\"dvd9cdjapan\"/><ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Kotomi Tsuda}}|\u6d25\u7530 \u30b3\u30c8\u30df|Tsuda Kotomi}} is Takatoshi's younger sister,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. p9}} who is in her final year of middle school at the beginning of the series and attends \u014csai the following year.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 27}} A cheerful girl, she is considerate and caring toward others, but is curious and enthusiastic about sexual matters - something she has in common with the title character in Ujiie's previous work {{Nihongo3|My Little Sister Is Going Through Puberty||Imouto wa Shishunki}}.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 9}}<ref name=\"ep5\"/> In one episode, when Takatoshi was sick, both she and Shino brought him adult manga.<ref name=\"ep5\"/> She is very close with her brother but, to Takatoshi's chagrin, her comments sometimes imply that they have an incestuous relationship.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 34, 39}} She gets along very well with the other girls and often asks for and gets help from them.\n\n;Kaede Igarashi\n;{{voiced by|[[Emiri Kat\u014d]]<ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Kaede Igarashi}}|\u4e94\u5341\u5d50 \u30ab\u30a8\u30c7|Igarashi Kaede}} is the head of the disciplinary committee at \u014csai Academy.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 3}} She has a strong sense of justice and morals, but has an [[wikt:androphobia|extreme fear of boys]]. This ends up being an issue because the school became co-ed after she enrolled.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 3}}<ref name=\"male\" group=\"n\">Igarashi reveals that the reason she is afraid of men is because, several years previously, when she practiced writing the kanji for 'male', a classmate asked if she was sexually frustrated.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 54}}</ref> As the series progresses, her androphobia lessens to a point: she is at ease when around Takatoshi, but not other men.\n\n;Sayaka Dejima\n;{{voiced by|[[Mutsumi Tamura]]<ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Sayaka Dejima}}|\u51fa\u5cf6 \u30b5\u30e4\u30ab|Dejima Sayaka}} is Aria's personal maid.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 11}} She is very protective of Aria and bears the key to her [[chastity belt]].{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 21}} She has a fetish for anything that Aria has touched or worn,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 16}} as well as unwashed underwear in general.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 31}}\n\n;Nene Todoroki\n;{{voiced by|[[Hekiru Shiina]]<ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Nene Todoroki}}|\u8f5f \u30cd\u30cd|Todoroki Nene}} is Suzu's friend and a member of the Robot Research Club.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 28}} She is as perverted as the rest of the girls,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 28}} as she often wears a [[Vibrator (sex toy)|vibrator]] during school hours or is seen working on such devices at her club.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 37}}\n\n;Kaoru Toki\n;{{voiced by|Miho Hino<ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Kaoru Toki}}|\u6642 \u30ab\u30aa\u30eb|Toki Kaoru}}  is Kotomi's first high school friend.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 36}} Even though Toki looks and sounds like a [[Juvenile delinquency|delinquent]], she is actually clumsy and shows no signs of a rebellious nature.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 36}} The only reason she leaves her shirt loose is because she once accidentally tucked it inside her underwear and was embarrassed about it.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 37}} She is a bit scatterbrained as she has a tendency to get lost and arrive late when meeting up with Kotomi.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 64, 84}} Her full name is revealed in the credits of the ''Seitokai Yakuindomo: The Movie.''\n\n;Chihiro Uomi\n;{{voiced by|[[Chiwa Sait\u014d]]<ref name=\"seitokai2 japanese cast\"/>}}\n:{{Nihongo|{{va|Chihiro Uomi}}|\u9b5a\u898b \u30c1\u30d2\u30ed}} nicknamed \"Womi\",{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 135}} {{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 415}} is the student council president of nearby Eiryou High School. She is introduced when her school visits \u014csai to exchange ideas. She and Shino discover they are much alike in thought and personality and thus they get along.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 113, 114}} She and Tsuda become in-laws of a sort when their respective cousins marry (Tsuda is the groom's cousin, Uomi is the bride's). Afterwards, she insists that Takatoshi call her Onee-chan and she addresses him as Taka-kun. She seems to view Takatoshi as a potential romantic interest, much to the consternation of some of the other girls.\n\n<!-- NEED SOURCE / SCRUB\n* {{Nihongo|Nozomi Mori|\u68ee \u30ce\u30be\u30df|Mori Nozomi}} {{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 300, 415}} is a second year student at Eriyou High School and the vice president of its student council, effectively making her Eriyou's equivalent of Takatoshi.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 300}} In the anime, she is voiced by [[Sumire Uesaka]].{{cn}}\n--->\n===Crossover characters===\nCharacters from Ujiie's previous works have made appearances in ''Seitokai''. Misaki Amano from {{Nihongo|''College Girl Tutor Hamanaka Ai''|\u5973\u5b50\u5927\u751f\u5bb6\u5ead\u6559\u5e2b\u6ff1\u4e2d\u30a2\u30a4|Joshidaisei Kateikyoushi Hamanaka Ai}} is Shino's ex-vice president in elementary school. Being in the same class as Shino in elementary school they both are of the same age with Amano now also being a high school student. Although both of them went to different high schools. Like Takatoshi, she acts as a ''tsukkomi'' for Shino's various jokes. The idol unit Triple Booking from Ujiie's work {{Nihongo|''Idol's Red Book''|\u30a2\u30a4\u30c9\u30eb\u306e\u3042\u304b\u307b\u3093|Aidoru no Aka Hon}} also make appearances.\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n''Seitokai Yakuindomo'' is written and illustrated by Tozen Ujiie. The manga began serialization in the June 2007 issue of [[Kodansha]]'s ''[[Magazine Special]]'' and ran in that magazine until the July 2008 issue,<ref name=\"vol1rel\"/> where it was thereafter transferred to Kodansha's ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Magazine]]'' starting with the 34th issue of 2008 sold in September.<ref name=\"vol2rel\"/> The first ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volume was released on August 12, 2008 under Kodansha's Sh\u014dnen Magazine KC [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]]; as of August 2019, 18 volumes have been released.\n\n==== Volume list ====\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n | OneLanguage = yes\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 1\n | RelDate         = August 12, 2008<ref name=\"vol1rel\">{{cite web|url=https://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product?item=0000016820|script-title=ja:\u751f\u5f92\u4f1a\u5f79\u54e1\u5171\uff08\uff11\uff09|trans-title=Seitokai Yakuindomo (1)|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-06-384030-8\n | ChapterList     =\n* Chapters 1\u201315 from ''Magazine Special''\n | Summary         =\nOusai Academy is a school that has recently turned co-ed. On his first day, [[#Takatoshi Tsuda|Takatoshi Tsuda]] is stopped by student body president [[#Shino Amakusa|Shino Amakusa]], who fixes his appearance. He meets secretary [[#Arai Shichijou|Aria Shichijou]] and treasurer [[#Suzu Hagimura|Suzu Hagimura]]. As he is late for class, Shino decides to give Takatoshi an excuse by making him the student body vice president. Shino shows Takatoshi around campus. Takatoshi looks over the school rules and observes the council's everyday happenings. Shino is interviewed by [[#Ranko Hata|Ranko Hata]] from the newspaper club. Takatoshi's classmate [[#Mustumi Mitsuba|Mutsumi Mitsuba]] forms a judo club. They do their midterms. They meet the perverted council advisor [[#Naruko Yokoshima|Yokoshima]]. Takatoshi visits Suzu at her house. Shino and Aria return from a class field trip. The council celebrates Shino\u2019s birthday. Shino and Takatoshi share an umbrella. Shino visits Takatoshi at home and meets his sister [[#Kotomi Tsuda|Kotomi]]. Shino and Aria have swimming class. Hata pursues some ghost stories. The council goes on a beach trip and stay overnight at a nearby inn. \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 2\n | RelDate         = May 15, 2009<ref name=\"vol2rel\">{{cite web|url=https://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product?item=0000016931|script-title=ja:\u751f\u5f92\u4f1a\u5f79\u54e1\u5171\uff08\uff12\uff09|trans-title=Seitokai Yakuindomo (2)|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-06-384142-8\n | ChapterList     =\n* Chapters 1\u201330 from ''Weekly Sh\u014dnen Magazine''\n | Summary         =\nThe council prepares for the school\u2019s sports day. Hata interviews Shino. A bug flies into the council room. [[#Kaede Igarashi|Kaede Igarashi]] of the Discipline Committee confronts the council on their summer beach trip. Shino helps the judo club with a match. The council prepares a school newsletter. Aria invites the council to her home. The school has a culture festival. The council cleans up their room. Aria hosts the council at her winter villa; they exchange Christmas presents and then do New Year\u2019s. Kotomi takes the entrance exams for Ousai. The council meets [[#Nene Todoroki|Nene Todoroki]] of the robotics research club. \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 3\n | RelDate         = January 15, 2010<ref name=\"vol3rel\">{{cite web|url=https://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product?item=0000017028|script-title=ja:\u751f\u5f92\u4f1a\u5f79\u54e1\u5171\uff08\uff13\uff09|trans-title=Seitokai Yakuindomo (3)|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-06-384240-1\n | ChapterList     =\n* Chapters 31\u201360 from ''Weekly Sh\u014dnen Magazine''\n | Summary         =\nHata visits Aria's estate. Kotomi starts her first year at Ousai. She introduces her friend [[#Toki|Toki]] who looks like a delinquent. The council girls change into summer uniforms and deal with the heat. Kotomi remarks on her reputation of being the sister of the vice president. The council hosts a school swim meet. The council girls visit Takatoshi and Kotomi to help clean their house, and stay over. Aria hosts a fireworks party. Shino gives a speech over the PA system. Suzu's dog visits school. The council inspects the different clubs. For career day, the school chooses Aria\u2019s maid [[#Sayaka Dejima|Dejima]] to visit the school. The council poses for art sketches, and prepares for another school festival.\n\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 4\n | RelDate         = August 17, 2010<ref name=\"vol4rel\">{{cite web|url=https://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product?item=0000017134|script-title=ja:\u751f\u5f92\u4f1a\u5f79\u54e1\u5171\uff08\uff14\uff09|trans-title=Seitokai Yakuindomo (4)|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|language